Q6_2_TEXT: The executive editors at the Maneater don’t seem to be focused on the big picture of the outlet. To their credit, I know they work hard and spend a lot of time editing stories but it takes up so much time that they don’t have any left over for preventative policies or growth policies. I think they need to focus on bigger picture issues at the Maneater. I don’t think the content we produce services our target audience or is what they want to read. I think engagement is down with our social media accounts because of our content. If this cycle continues, our readers won’t engage and won’t trust us. I don’t feel as though I can bring these concerns to them because when I do bring concerns to them, nothing changes.
